content:
The `Value()` function is used to convert text data into a numeric value that can be used in mathematical calculations.

Without the `Value()` function, the system treats the values in the "ScheduledEEAmount" and "ScheduledERAmount" columns as text. If you try to perform addition directly on text values, it will not work as expected. The `Value()` function tells the system to interpret the text as a number, allowing the `Add()` function to correctly calculate the sum.
